The paper deals with clustering problems and algorithms, which are typically studied in the subfield of computer science known as data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of same-cluster queries is a novel approach to clustering, which falls under the category of active learning and query-based learning, making cs.AI another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the running time of the algorithm, which involves analyzing the complexity of the problem, making cs.IT a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper specifically deals with the correlation clustering problem, which is a well-known problem in the field of computational complexity (cs.CC).
